    <activity>
        <statement>

            <p>
                <term>Work in Groups</term>
            </p>

            <p>
                In real life, individuals and institutions make financial decisions that involve borrowing or deferred payment. These decisions are influenced by interest, repayment time, and affordability.
            </p>

            <p>
                In this activity, you will investigate how hire purchase arrangements affect the total cost of goods and how financial institutions structure repayment systems to generate interest.
            </p>

            <p>
                Identify and discuss situations in your community where people purchase goods on credit and end up paying more than the cash price. Record your findings in the table below.
            </p>

            <tabular top="medium" bottom="medium" right="medium" left="medium">
                <row header="yes">
                    <cell>Item Bought on Hire Purchase</cell>
                    <cell>Observed Financial Impact</cell>
                    <cell>Reason for Extra Cost</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Motorbike</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Television</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>Smartphone</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>

            <p>
                <alert>Case Study Analysis:</alert>
            </p>

            <p>
                A motorbike is sold at a cash price of Ksh <m>120,000</m>. A buyer pays a deposit of <m>25\%</m> and the balance is repaid under a hire purchase agreement where simple interest is charged at <m>12\%</m> per annum for <m>2</m> years.
            </p>

            <p>
                In groups, you are required to:
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>Determine the deposit and outstanding balance.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Compute the total interest charged on the balance.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Determine the total hire purchase price.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Compare the hire purchase price with the cash price and compute the percentage increase.</p>
                    </li>
                    
                </ol>
            </p>

            <p>
                <alert>Higher Order Thinking Task:</alert>
            </p>

            <p>
                Suppose the repayment period is extended from 2 years to 3 years while keeping all other conditions constant.
            </p>

            <p>
                Discuss:
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>How does the total cost change?</li>
                    <li>What happens to the interest charged?</li>
                    <li>Is the buyer financially better or worse off? Justify mathematically and logically.</li>
                </ol>
            </p>

            <p>
                <alert>Decision-Making Task:</alert>
            </p>

            <p>
                Compare the hire purchase option with a cash purchase scenario where the buyer must save for 2 years before purchasing the same motorbike. Discuss:
            </p>

            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>Opportunity cost of waiting versus buying immediately</li>
                    <li>Financial burden of instalments versus saving discipline</li>
                    <li>Which option is economically rational and why</li>
                </ol>
            </p>

        </statement>
    </activity>

